Reducing speed is a </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">key to accident severity reduction and thus to perceptions of safe streets</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> and changing the environment is another</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Here I select th</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ose</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> sections most </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">germane</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> for this Inquiry</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.  Although the work </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">dates from 1992</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> the rate of incident remains below the thre</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">shold of Highways Authority reaction too </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">often, it’s as if the cyclist is expected to bear the risk as a normal cost.  </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">In</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> our research </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">incidents, and their locations, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">suggest a more important role for segregation </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">on</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> the road than </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">attention being focused </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">mainly</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> at junctions</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">Cyclists under threat: a survey of Oxford cyclists' perceptions of risk</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> HEALTH EDUCATION JOURNAL VOL 51/4, 1992, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Sissons Joshi, Smith, </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.3.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Description: - </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">FIFTY regular cyclists in Oxford kept a diary over</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">14 days in early June 1992 </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">and recorded 404</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">incidents which made them feel at risk. </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">This</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">constituted a rate of 0.9 incidents per cyclist per</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">day of cycling</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">. Fear was mostly induced by</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">other road users. Cars were blamed in 45.3 per</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">cent of the incidents, followed by buses (14.6 per</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">cent), vans (8.4 per cent) and other cyclists (6.4</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">per cent). Buses make up less than 5 per cent of</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the city-centre traffic but were involved in 27 per</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">cent of the incidents rated as 'moderately to extremely</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">threatening' by the cyclists. </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">Seventy-one</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">per ce</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">nt of the incidents took place in 'straight</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">-</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">ahead'</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">sit</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">uations with only 19 per cent at </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">junctions and roundabouts</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">…</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">3.3.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">Discussion</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">: </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The finding that, for this group of regular cyclists,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">threatening incidents on the roads were experienced at the</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">rate of nearly </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">one incident per cyclist per day cycled,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">suggests that there is likely to be a considerable disincentive</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">to cycling. </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">…</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-18.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 60.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0.7pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The picture of risk derived from the diaries deviates somewhat from local accident figures. It is not clear what weight should be given </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">to the official statistics on accidents as it is well accepted that cycle accidents, including those involving serious injury, are massively under-reported </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 60.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0.7pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 60.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0.7pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">The discrepancies between the figures obtained from the diaries and those of police record data ar</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">e reminders of the subjectivity of accident notation and witness testimony</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 40.35pt; orphans:0; text-indent:11.85pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 60.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0.7pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">If a cyclist swerves to avoid</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">an unexpected pothole, an </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ensuing accident</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> with an offside</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">vehicle could be attributed either to </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">cyclist error</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, to motorist</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">error or to road conditi</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ons.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 60.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0.7pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 60.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0.7pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">The diary figures also deviate from national accident figures produced by the Department of Transport, which give more emphasis to vehicles turning left and right, and less emphasis to parked vehicles</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 60.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0.7pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 60.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0.7pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">In its document Pedal Cyclist Casualties-1, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the Department of Transport does warn the reader about the possible unreliability </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">of their</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> data due to the underreporting of cycle accidents to the police</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, which</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> form the basis for their figures.  Furthermore, local figures may well differ from national fi</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">gures because of variations in traffic density and type, and local provision (or lack of provision) for cyclists. Also it must be noted that the diarists in the study reported here were over 23-years-old and were experienced and regular cyclists. As such t</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">hey were likely to anticipate the infamous problem areas for cyclists - that is, junctions and roundabouts. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 40.35pt; orphans:0; text-indent:11.85pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 59.4pt; orphans:0; text-indent:1.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">However</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">it is possible that cycle proficiency education has overestimated</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">the risk to cyclists at intersections and roundabouts and</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">underestimated the risk in straight-ahead situations. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 59.4pt; orphans:0; text-indent:1.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 59.4pt; orphans:0; text-indent:1.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">Hospital</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">-</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">based</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">studies of cycle accidents not only suggest a much</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">larger number of accidents but also a different pattern of</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">accidents than that indicated by police records. It is</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">interesting to note </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">that an Australian study examining the</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">characteristics of fatal, as compared to total, bicycle accidents</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">finds that fatal accidents are less likely to be at</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">intersections than a</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">re non-fatal accidents.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">We were not expecting the result concerning the locati</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">on of </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">incidents and subsequently undertook a broader study with a balance of diarists representing a typical traffic mix.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">A diary study of the risk perceptions of road users</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">, HEALTH</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, RISK &amp; SOCIETY, VOL. 3, NO. 3, 2001, SISSONS JOSHI, SENIOR &amp; SMITH. pp26</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">1 – 279</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; text-indent:-25.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.4.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">(from </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">Discussion</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, p 274)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 58.7pt; orphans:0; text-indent:1.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Data from our previous study suggested that junctions and roundabouts were not perceived</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">to be as numerically hazardous by the cycle diarists as would be expected from their</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">prominence in local and national accident figures. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 58.7pt; orphans:0; text-indent:1.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 58.7pt; orphans:0; text-indent:1.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">A similar picture emerges from this study</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">in which only 35.4% of incidents reported by cyclists, and 37.5% of incidents involving</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">cyclists reported by other vehicles, occurred at junctions, excluding rou</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">ndabouts.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 58.7pt; orphans:0; text-indent:1.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 58.7pt; orphans:0; text-indent:1.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">This</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">contrasts with Oxfordshire Road Casualty figures (Oxfordshire County Council, 1993),</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">which report that 68% of cycle accidents occur at junctions. It is well known that cycle</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">accidents are under-represented in accident figures (Mills, 1989)</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> but we are addressing here</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the pattern rather than the absolute number of accidents. National figures (Department of</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Transport, 1992) also suggest that at least two-thirds of cycle accidents occur at junctions.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">  </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">We suggest that these official figures almo</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">st certainly relate more to the classification of</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">accidents than to the nature of what is happening on the road. The police STATS 19 records</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">classify an accident as occurring at a junction irrespective of whether the manoeuvre of either</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">vehicle concerned i</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">nvolved the junction or merely happened in the vicinity of a junction.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 58.7pt; orphans:0; text-indent:1.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 58.7pt; orphans:0; text-indent:1.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">With this query in mind, we asked the Department of Transport’s Directorate of Statistics to</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">analyse national pedal cycle casualty figures by cross-tabulating cyclists’ actions with </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">the</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">actions of those involved in accidents with them. Of the 25,421 cycle accidents in 1991,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">13.8% involved cyclists turning right or left and a further 28.9% involved other vehicles</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">turning right or left. This suggests that only 42.7% of cycle accidents i</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">nvolve turns at</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">junctions, which is considerably closer to estimates in the diary data than the usual two-thirds</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">figure quoted</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">The major manoeuvre of other vehicles which cyclists reported in the current study was</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">being overtaken too closely in a straight</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">-ahead situation</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 58.7pt; orphans:0; text-indent:1.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 58.7pt; orphans:0; text-indent:1.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">It is notable that an Australian</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">study, examining the characteristics of fatal as compared to total cycle accidents, finds that</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">fatal accidents are less likely to be at intersections than are non-fatal accidents (Hoque,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">1990). </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Our data</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> also accord with the British Medical Association’s (1992) review, which</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">comments that most adult cyclist fatalities are caused by a vehicle approaching from</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">behind </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">—which presumably includes errors in overtaking. The Highway Code (Department of</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Environmen</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">t, Transport and the Regions, 1999b) inf</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">orms motorists that they should </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">‘give</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">[cyclists] at least as much room as you would give a car’ (p. 18), although the accompanying</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">illustration suggests a less generous margin of overtaking than did the illustration </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">in the 1993</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">edition (Department </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">of Transport, 1993). The cyclists in our study clearly felt that they were</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">not given the margin they required by passing motor vehicles, particularly buses. It is possible</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">that buses overtake cycles with no narrower a margin</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> than cars do, but threaten cyclists more</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">on account of their greater size. A film record would be needed to establish whether cyclists’</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">perceptions of risk relate more to the size, speed or position of the passing vehicle.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">3.4.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">(</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">from</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> Conclusions </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Page 277)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">…</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">However, while the successful shared use of public space will depend partly on road users’</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">attitudes and behaviour, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">it will also depend on the imaginative implementation of road design</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">that can protect the vulnerable from the manoeuvres and speed of the le</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">ss vulnerable. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Indeed,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">in his analysis of accident causation, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">Wagenaar (1992) points out that risk-taking behaviour</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">can be located predominantly at the strategic end of the system—that is, amongst the</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">decision makers who structure the system. This </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">implies that the nature of the risk environment</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">lies in the hands of those who plan our roads rather than those who use them.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Experience in the Netherlands reveals the extent to which engineering solutions can provide</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">a safer space for cyclists and walker</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> (Preston, 1990; Tolley, 1990).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 41.25pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-0.7pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The likelihood of risk on the highway being </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">located</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> significantly</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> as </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the outcome of planning the road, and/or the degree to which politicians </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">understand, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">demand or manage the engineering outcomes is a stark conclusion </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">regarding</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> the risks perceived, and imposed on vulnerable road users.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.5.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">But also hopeful because the production of these outcomes could be changed with rapidity.  As has been the case in Germany, the Netherlands etc.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The predominant response in our British </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">experience is twofold,</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.6.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The pitifully small modal share taken by </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">cycling</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.6.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The belief among many people cycling that ‘defensive’ cycling has to be learnt, to cope with conditions on the road.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 86.4pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-32.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.6.2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">This then has the added problem that </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">these ‘coping’ cyclists in som</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">e way define how cycling should be done.  </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">This</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> presents a b</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">arrier to using a bike for many;</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> for the overwhelming majority reported in the ESPRC - UW&amp;C research, who do not expect to</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> and who will not</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> ‘battle’ with motorised traffic.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 86.4pt; text-indent:-32.4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.6.2.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">For many years divisio</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">n</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> within cycling advocacy between vehicular cyclists and those who favour better infrastructure </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">are</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> deeply unhelpful. Advocating for the wishes of existing cyclists, a minority outlier population, is not the way to make cycling appeal to wider swathes of </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the population. This does of course result in a tension, as it is not unreasonable for cycling advocacy groups to represent their members, but it is a tension that can I think be fairly easily resolved. There is no need for a dichotomous approach, and it i</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">s perfectly feasible to support the needs of existing cyclists while also pushing for decent infrastructure, as well as wider factors that support less confident cyclists.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 86.4pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-32.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.6.2.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">In practice and even with years </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">of </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">experience it feels simply impossible to </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">con</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">sistent</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">ly</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> take a ‘vehicular cyclist’ approach.  I base this comment on personal experience and observation of others.  </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">E.G. travelling from Paddington Station to Smithfield, and return, t</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">here are many situations where the ambiguity of the road makes it dif</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ficult to avoid being in a narrow space alongside</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">/between</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> moving vehicles.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">3.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">What is illustrated by this section is the gulf between highways practice and a highways </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">environment where cycling is enabled by the physical environment.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.54pt; orphans:0; padding-left:4.46pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The perceptions of those managing the Highway are clear to an extent in the </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">design </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">outcomes, the design proposals and subsequently the built project.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">  Where does the thinking derive?  It is not at all the same everywhere – in nearby continental Europe for </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">instance.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">4.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The thinking and presumption/expectations of much of the </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Britain </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">has been deeply </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">influenced</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> by </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">thinking</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> about the road environment </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">dating </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">from WW11</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, then</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> the influential</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Traffic in Towns</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> report of </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">63, which effectively promoted car use at the </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">expense of urban demolition, segregating motorised movement from the life of the urban area.  Residential Road Layout Guidance</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> followed, ‘DB32’ of 1977 </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> 2007, cementing</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> the idea that residential areas should be quiet and free from extraneous traffic</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> using</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> culs-de-sac</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.  A comforting concept but one which was both a travesty of the original Radburn, NJ, where the density is around 4 Dw</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ellings</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">/</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">cre, as well as a de-facto </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">effect of</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">limiting</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> walking </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">- </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">by distancing retail </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">and other destinations in</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">to separate ag</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">glomerations;</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> ma</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">king</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">bus travel difficult to support;</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> and result</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ing in a bleak, high-</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">speed environmen</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">t in which to cycle.  The model</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> presented by Stevenage and Milton Keynes </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">has</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> been found not </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">support cycling because the provision is </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">added</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> after</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">layout</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">concept </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">design</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> rather than </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">part of</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> it</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">4.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">A layout </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">conceived </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">for </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">car</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">s </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">convenience whilst moving </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">is most unlikely ever to be convenient or desirable for cycling whereas the ‘traditional city’ London in large part for instance, is connected and with a ch</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">oice of destination on offer and where the bike is frequently the most convenient and quickest travel mode</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.  The withdrawal of DB32 and </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">replacement</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> by </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Manual for Streets</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">’ in 2007</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> is an important milepost in urban design.  A connected system</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> where most roads will inevitably be ‘quiet’, where connectivity can reduce the need to use a car, and where the bike performs competitively in convenience and quickness, is posited in the current guidance.  But at the point of publication tw</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">o unfortunate </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">problems appeared:</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">4.2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> Banking crisis led to house-building collapsing and thus practice and debate using the new guidance has faltered</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, and</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> in addition </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">4.2.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> guidance ‘left open a door’, to the </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">continued, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">inappropriate </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">reference to</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> DMRB, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Design Manual fo</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">r Roads and Bridges</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">’ </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the Highways Agency’s </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">design guide</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">  It was not until the publication of </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Manual for Streets 2, wider application of the principles’ </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">(</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">2010</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, that DMRB’s inappropriateness is substituted. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">4.2.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">I fear that the freely available MfS has a wide</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">r distribution than the expensive MfS2.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">4.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The consequence of the ubiquity of DMRB in practice is that thinking about users and facilities is ‘controlled’, to some significant extent, by concern over vehicular speed, volume and avoiding congestion of motor </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">traffic.  In comparison the German Roads Guidance, RASt06 (which I translated into English</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> for the publisher</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">) has</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> since the early 1980s</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> taken the ‘revolutionary’ view that </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the place’ and the activities taking place alongside any road </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">are</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> primary conside</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ration</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> in the road design process.  The German approach was itself heavily influenced by Dutch thinking and practice </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">during</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> the 70s and in 1981 West</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Ger</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">many </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">‘adopted’ Dutch </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">guidance</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> as they rewrote their own </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">manual.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">4.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Following the Times newspaper campaign </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">and the existing interest of the current Government</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> a range of</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> new</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> funding </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">resources</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> have been provided.  In the case of the Cycle Safety Fund I wish to adumbrate a case in Oxfordshire of quite atrocious inability to design a fitting response and worse still, being able to comprehend and react to external criticism.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">4.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Here is the body of a </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">recently published letter</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> of a group of local experts: -</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><div style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; clear:both; margin:0pt"><p style="margin:0pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt; padding-top:1pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">We learn from Oxford Times Letters (2/01/14) that the County is pressing on with its unbelievable design for the Wootton Road roundabout, Abingdon:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><a href="http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/opinion/letters/10902309.New_cycle_route_is_both_risky_and_ill_conceived/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline">http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/opinion/letters/10902309.New_cycle_route_is_both_risky_and_ill_conceived/</span></a><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic"> This</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic"> follows my objection 17/10/13 that the design, using special ‘Cycle Sa</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">fety Fund’ grant, was without merit:</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic"> </span><a href="http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/yourtown/abingdon/10734790.Fresh_look_at___300k_cycle_safety_project/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline">http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/yourtown/abingdon/10734790.Fresh_look_at___300k_cycle_safety_project/</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">Since then we’ve met officers on site, submitted a comprehensive report and further criticised a slightly modified scheme. </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">Yet </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">"The cabinet member… informed the meeting that the only place in Oxfordshire the council could identify as qualifying for a </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">Government grant was this area on Wootton Road. </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">Openly admitting that the scheme was flawed he continued, overruling safety concerns in order to spend the money before the April deadline."</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">When budgets are shrunk and e.g. schools are crying out for zebr</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">a crossings for their pupils, this is a debacle. </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">To willfully misspend £300,000, including misusing c£200,000 of DfT’s Grant in the process, is tantamount to theft. </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">Is it possible that County Transport Planners and Engineers are so diminished by cuts t</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">hat there is inadequate management will and design skill? </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">Little response has followed the consultation.  A ‘Cyclox’ member produced a better scheme, earlier on, only to be ignored. </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">The design is an incompetent response to a problem, which is real enou</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">gh. </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">A County defence that an expensive and poorly located Toucan crossing ‘has to remain, or DfT would withdraw funding’, is spurious.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">It is irresponsible to spend money just because its there, it belongs to us all. </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">Perhaps the money should be given </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">back to DfT/Treasury, or at least leave requested to produce an effective scheme.  In my understanding of the DfT assessor's comments, a rethink was called for anyway.  It is not too late to do something effective; it’s the will that is lacking.</span></p></div><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">4.5.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">W</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">hilst the</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> concern here could be </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">dismissed</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> as parochial, the case will be repeated through the hundreds of schemes receiv</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">such </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">funding</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, why? :-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 86.4pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-32.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">4.5.1.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">An officer is charged with developing a response to an accident problem but perhaps with little expectation of funding</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">  A</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> Government fund appears</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">It i</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">s grasped even though the design is </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">perhaps simplistic</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> if worthy</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.  Essentially</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> rather than </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">moving</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> away from </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> ‘DMRB’ style roundabout</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">on the periphery of an urban area </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">- </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">with people travelling by </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">bike</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> to nursery, school,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> college </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">etc.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, a proposal to partly remove cycl</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ists from the road has ensu</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ed.  </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">However</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">cost engineering has removed the potential benefits and attractiveness of the </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">design, which</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> is now decimated.  An inappropriate single Toucan remains, adding cost and inducing delay.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">  Whilst I am sure th</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> problem was, or became </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">recognised</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> within the Engineering </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Dept.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> of Oxfordshire </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">County</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> Council, there was no will to </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">jetison</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> the design </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">tim</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">e </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">already </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">expended </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">in order</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> to reconsider the problem, which </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">remains</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> soluble.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">4.5.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Even generous central support is </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">squandered</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> in this example.  ‘Localism’ has resulted in wastefulness.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">4.5.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">What is needed is some kind of ‘Roads Ombudsman’</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, to act as a design revi</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ew</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">er.  The CABE-</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Design Council system needs</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">be </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">replicated</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> for Highways design.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.54pt; orphans:0; padding-left:4.46pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">I suggest that a roads network that applies segregated provision to all threatening, busy or fast roads</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">planned</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.  Using the kind of </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">application </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">chart already known, e.g.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> as found on London Cycling Campaign’s website and other locations.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">5.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The argument, even fear, expressed by many campaigners that such segregated provision is too difficult, costly or controversial is falsely based.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">5.1.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">If one takes time to understand the development of facilities to be found in continental countries it can be seen that by adopting the concept of a </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">safe, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">physically segregated (but on-line) provision</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> the attainment of the concept may be achieved in a numb</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">er of ways, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">using</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> normal processes.  </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Making</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> cycling provisions that enable use by anyone is not rocket science.  Any highways engineer could do it</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">perhaps </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">as demonstrated in Cologne where </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the City Engineer told a group I led</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">: “the politicians </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">wanted peopl</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">e to be able to use a bike, so this is what we have done …”.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">5.1.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Compared with the </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">massive </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">funding used to effectively enthrall the population to the car, costs can be negligible.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">5.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Essentially </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">one</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> start</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> with </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">idea</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">direct, coherent, continuous provision and </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">initially </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">separated by (mandatory) lines, (</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">with </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">parking control</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">outside</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> of these mandatory lines</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">).</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">  Physical segregation </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">can then</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> follow as road</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">renewal</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> take</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> place.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">5.2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">The busiest roads are replaced in cities on </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">approximately 10-20 year cycles. </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">W</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ithin a generation or t</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">wo, we coul</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">d </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">reach</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> Denmark's </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">situation now and </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">approach</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> the Netherlands' </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">level of provision</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 86.4pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-32.4pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">5.2.1.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">he </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">30 year period</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> of the now withdrawn </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">cul-de-sac and dis</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">tributor road’ thinking from 1977 </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">has been </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">re</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">markably effective</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> around the country, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">and thus </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the country’</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> main routes could be transformed </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">in a similar timespan</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.  Only thinking is demanded.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">5.2.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Inevitably some special attention will need to applied to major junctions with their tonnes of concrete, but even these need repair, remodeling and rethinking over time.  The period required seems ‘long’ </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">in prospect</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, but the renewal process is </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">happening co</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">ntinuously,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">within the </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">span</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> of a few Parliaments the transformation could be complete.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">5.2.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Changing the new towns and 70s-onwards estates and their distributor road</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, if desired,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> is a big design task, </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">some regeneration projects</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">mostly involving turning houses a</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">round</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">!</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">  But for London and most of </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Britain</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">, making cycling possible for all could be achieved for </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">the proverbial </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">peanuts</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">And</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> if we started 'now'</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> with the decision to make cycling prov</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">isions that were useable by all it could become a reality in reasonable</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> time.</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">Short</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline"> CV</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Consultant, 'Graham Paul Smith: Urban Design', </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Studied</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Fine Art and Urban Design, he is a</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">commuting cyclist and a</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> former </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">amateur </span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">racing cyclist,</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">Employment</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Associate and formerly Principal/Senior Lecturer </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Department of Architecture, Oxford Brookes University: Post Graduate Diploma Architecture &amp; </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">Joint Centre</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt"> for Urban Design, 1970 to 2007. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size:9pt">He was a part-time tutor in th